# Testing Conventions

> **Tests are not optional and must never be only happy-path.** Every test file must include success cases, error/failure cases, and edge cases.

## General Rules

- Every test must include: success cases + error cases + edge cases
- Minimum 4+ test cases per function/method
- Use mocks/stubs for external dependencies
- Tests must be deterministic and isolated
{{#if_flag "has_backend" profile}}
## Backend Tests

- Test files live alongside the code they test
- Use table-driven / parameterized tests
- Test: happy path + validation failures + not found + auth errors + internal errors
- Run: `{{profile.test.unit_cmd}}`

```
// Minimum test cases per handler/service:
// 1. success case with valid input
// 2. not found / validation error
// 3. unauthorized / forbidden
// 4. internal / database error
```
{{/if_flag}}{{#if_flag "has_frontend" profile}}
## Frontend Tests

- Test files: `__tests__/` directories mirroring source structure
- Use component testing library (RTL, Vue Test Utils, etc.)
- Test: rendering + user interaction + success API + error API + edge cases
- Minimum 5+ test cases per component

```
// Minimum per component:
// 1. renders correctly with data
// 2. handles user interaction (click, input)
// 3. success API call → correct UI update
// 4. error API call → shows error state
// 5. edge case: empty list / null / loading state
```
{{/if_flag}}{{#if profile.test.e2e_tool}}
## E2E Tests ({{profile.test.e2e_tool}})

- Test complete user journeys
- Test error flows (invalid inputs, permission denied, network errors)
- Use `data-testid` attributes for selectors
- Minimum 2 scenarios per feature: 1 success journey + 1 error/edge journey
{{/if}}
